body:
Hello,
I have a verilog file of gates with one level of hierarchy I want to flatten away.
If I use flatten command with module name as argument it seems not to work as I expect.

```
read_verilog gate.v

# Version 1
# This pair will flatten my_or2 away and remove all other gates like "dont_flatten_me" gate
#hierarchy -top flatten_selected
#flatten

# Version 2
# This pair will not flatten my_or2 away
#hierarchy -top flatten_selected
#flatten flatten_selected

# Version 3
# This version without hierarchy commands doesn't flatten my_or2 away
flatten flatten_selected

clean -purge
dump
stat
shell
```

```
module flatten_selected (A, B, Y);
  input  A, B;
  output Y;

  my_or2 U1 (.A(A), .B(B), .Y(Y));

endmodule

module dont_flatten_me (A, B, Y);
  input  A, B;
  output Y;

  my_or2 U1 (.A(A), .B(B), .Y(Y));

endmodule


module my_or2 (A, B, Y);
  input A, B;
  output Y;
        
  or my_sub ( Y, A, B );
    
endmodule
```

